2 SENATE BILL 728
1 1. THE COMMUNITY COLLEGE LOCATED IN THE COUNTY
2 WHERE THE APPLICANT LIVES;
3 2. THE REGIONAL COMMUNITY COLLEGE LOCATED IN
4 THE REGION WHERE THE APPLICANT LIVES; OR
5 3. A COMMUNITY COLLEGE IN THE STATE THAT HAS AN
6 ON–CAMPUS RESIDENTIAL FACILITY FOR STUDENTS; AND
7 (II) 1. Enrolls as a candidate for a vocational certificate, a
8 certificate, or an associate’s degree or participates in a registered apprenticeship after
9 graduating from a high school or successfully completing a GED in the State[:
10 (i) Except as provided in item (ii) of this item, at the community
11 college located in the county or, in the case of a regional community college, in the region,
12 where the applicant lives; or
13 (ii) At a community college in the State that has an on–campus
14 residential facility for students]; OR
15 2. A. ENROLLS AS A CANDIDATE FOR A VOCATIONAL
16 CERTIFICATE, A CERTIFICATE, OR AN ASSOCIATE’S DEGREE OR PARTICIPATES IN A
17 REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP AFTER GRADUATING FROM DELMAR HIGH SCHOOL
18 IN DELMAR, DELAWARE; AND
19 B. IS A RESIDENT OF DELMAR, MARYLAND;
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
21 1, 2026.
